### Elasticsearch Version

8.12+

### Installed Plugins

_No response_

### Java Version

_bundled_

### OS Version

_any_

### Problem Description

This bug has existed for quite some time. An example of this behavior can be seen `aggregate_metric_double`. When originally written, it was specified that `notInMultiFields(CONTENT_TYPE)`. This prevents the mapper from being part of a multi-field, NOT from having multi fields.

Then when calling a PUT with `aggregate_metric_double` and `fields`, we just drop `fields` on the floor and do not validate.

### Steps to Reproduce

```
PUT mult-test
{
  "mappings": {
    "properties": {
      "asdf": {
        "type": "aggregate_metric_double",
        "metrics": [ "min", "max", "sum", "value_count" ],
        "default_metric": "max",
        "fields": {
          "a": {
            "type": "text"
          }
        }
      }
    }
  }
}

GET mult-test
```

Note how the mapping is missing the multi-field `a`. This is confusing behavior.

